trans-unit.source: Appliedline™ is the software development branch of AA Advanced Information Technology PLC® (AAAIT), specialized in software development for goverment, corporate and individual organizations. AAAIT PLC has been in the business of IT hardware and service deliverables since 2006 before incubating its software development unit in 2009. In 2015, AAAIT PLC decided to let its software development unit run independently as Appliedline with a vision to be incorporated by 2020.

Our Core values are precision, synergy, professionalism and continuous learning. Our goal is to exceed the expectations of every client by offering outstanding customer service and great value that puts their bussiness at a competitive advantage as well as eliminate outlined bussiness problems.

At Appliedline, we value our customers hence we invest a lot in hiring developers that have solid and vast experience in the software development industry. Our team have deep industry knowledge in technologies such as ASP.NET MVC, .NET Core, AngularJS & Angular, NodeJS, cross-platform and hybrid app development (Xamarin and Cordova), UX and UI design, RDBMS & NoSql databases, Microsoft Azure and many more.

In order to meet the demand of our ever growing clientele, Appliedline maintains a wide range of technology development programmes to keep its employees up-to-date with the latest tools and resources in the software development industry. Technical expertise along with vast and deep industry knowledge makes Appliedline the ideal choice for a software development company to provide custom software services and products to your company.

CargoCanal is a platform enhances management as well as improve the logistics service of the country by facilitating the information exchange between maritime, freight forwarders, consignees and other stakeholders in the freight forwarding industry. It is also designed to help other stakeholders like national banks, customs and ministry of transportation to address the issues they experience relating to import and export. This service was launched on the 25th of October at UNECA with guests invited from different sectors of the industry.

As mentioned in the ceremony "Ethiopia is 170th among 176 countries in the quality of logistics service." One of the main reasons for this is lack of fast and real time information exchange between stakeholders and actors in the industry. CargoCanal shows the location and status of each cargo; it will help solve many problems in the industry.

At the launching ceremony, the Director General of Ethiopian Maritime Affairs Authority (EMMA), Mr. Mekonen Abera, said "logistics without information is impossible. The platform we are launching today is going to digitalize and modernize the logistcs service." Mr. Alemayehu Tolosa, one of the investors in the industry, said "we were not be able to trace our cargo and it was very hard to get our cargo after being moved to one of the dry ports, but now we can get such kind of information near real time."
